@startuml System Diagram for Game Selector Project

!define AWSPUML https://raw.githubusercontent.com/awslabs/aws-icons-for-plantuml/v18.0/dist
!include AWSPUML/AWSCommon.puml

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam componentStyle uml2

actor User
component "User Interface" as UI
component "Data Collection Module" as DCM
component "Recommendation Engine" as RE
database "Game Database" as DB
component "Feedback Loop" as FL

' Data Flows
User --> UI : User inputs (system, genres, favorites, history)
UI --> DCM : Raw user data
DCM --> RE : Processed user preferences
RE --> DB : Query for game data
DB --> RE : Game metadata (genres, ratings, etc.)
RE --> UI : Personalized recommendations
UI --> User : Display recommendations
UI --> FL : User feedback (likes/dislikes)
FL --> RE : Refinement data for algorithm tuning

' Testing Flows
actor "Unit Tests" as UT
actor "Integration Tests" as IT
actor "User Acceptance Tests" as UAT
actor "Performance Tests" as PT

UT --> DCM : Test data parsing
UT --> RE : Test recommendation algorithms
UT --> DB : Test data retrieval
IT --> DCM : Test data flow to RE
IT --> RE : Test integration with DB
IT --> UI : Test output rendering
UAT --> UI : Simulate user interactions
PT --> UI : Load testing (concurrent users)
PT --> RE : Stress test algorithms
PT --> DB : Test large dataset handling

note right of UI : Handles input/output and feedback collection
note right of DCM : Processes and validates user inputs
note right of RE : Core AI logic for recommendations
note right of DB : Stores game information
note right of FL : Improves recommendations over time

@enduml